## Context Engine (CCE)

Use `context_search` instead of reading files directly when exploring the codebase, answering code questions, or understanding how things work.

Use `Read` or direct file open only when editing a known file or when exact full file content is needed.

If `context_search` is unavailable, say CCE/MCP is unavailable and use normal search/read tools as fallback.

Use:

- `expand_chunk` for full source of a compressed result
- `related_context` for calls/imports
- `session_recall` before non-trivial architecture/design questions
- `record_decision` after non-obvious choices
- `record_code_area` after meaningful file work

Respond compactly. Show only changed lines with 3 lines of context when suggesting code changes.
